4 SYNOPSIS:
5 This bill would authorize the city council of a
6 Class 1 municipality to set the salary of the mayor.
7 This bill would increase the expense allowance
8 of the mayor of a Class 1 municipality to $10,000 per
9 month.
10 This bill would also repeal Act 84-618 of the
11 1984 Regular Session (Acts 1984, p. 1256) and Sections
12 11-43-86.1 and 45-37A-52.93, Code of Alabama 1975,
13 providing for the compensation of the Mayor of
14 Birmingham.
15
16
17 A BILL
18 TO BE ENTITLED
19 AN ACT
20
21 Relating to Class 1 municipalities; to authorize the
22 city council to set the salary of the mayor; to amend Sections
23 11-43-80 and 11-43-86, Code of Alabama 1975, to further
24 provide for the mayor's compensation; to make conforming
25 changes; and to repeal Act 84-618 of the 1984 Regular Session
26 (Acts 1984, p. 1256), providing for an expense allowance for
27 the mayor of a Class 1 municipality; Section 11-43-86.1, Code
28 of Alabama 1975, providing for an increase in the salary of
