of Alabama 1975, providing for an increase in the salary of
SB375 INTRODUCED
29 the mayor in a Class 1 municipality; and Section 45-37A-52.93,
30 Code of Alabama 1975, providing for the salary of the Mayor of
31 Birmingham.
32 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
33 Section 1. (a) The annual salary of the mayor of a
34 Class 1 municipality for the duration of his or her term shall
35 be set by the city council in an amount that is no less than
36 two hundred twenty thousand dollars ($220,000) per year. The
37 salary of the mayor shall not increase or decrease during his
38 or her term.
39 (b) The mayor shall receive the annual salary payable
40 in monthly installments at the end of each month, the
41 installments to be paid at the same rate for any portion of
42 the month during which the mayor holds the office at the rate
43 provided in subsection (a).
44 (c) The salary provided in subsection (a) shall
45 supersede any other salary provided by law.
46 Section 2. Sections 11-43-80 and 11-43-86, Code of
47 Alabama 1975, are amended to read as follows:
